#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 3. Tatiyavagga → māravaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn4.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Māra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Sambahulasutta"
msgstr "21. Several"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.118"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.259"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati silāvatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans near Silāvatī."

# This passage exposes how poor “dwelling” is as a rendering of viharati in such cases.
msgctxt "sn4.21:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavato avidūre appamattā ātāpino "
"pahitattā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time several mendicants were meditating not far from the Buddha, "
"diligent, keen, and resolute."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā brāhmaṇavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā mahantena jaṭaṇḍuvena "
"ajinakkhipanivattho jiṇṇo gopānasivaṅko ghurughurupassāsī udumbaradaṇḍaṃ "
"gahetvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked manifested in the form of a brahmin with a large matted "
"dreadlock, wearing an antelope hide. He was old, bent double, wheezing, and "
"held a staff made of cluster fig tree wood. He went up to those mendicants "
"and said:"

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.5"
msgid ""
"“daharā bhavanto pabbajitā susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā "
"paṭhamena vayasā anikkīḷitāvino kāmesu."
msgstr ""
"“You’ve gone forth while young, reverends. You’re black-haired, blessed with "
"youth, in the prime of life, and you’ve never flirted with sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.6"
msgid "Bhuñjantu bhavanto mānusake kāme."
msgstr "Enjoy human sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.7"
msgid "Mā sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvitthā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Don’t give up what you see in the present life to chase after what takes "
"time.”"

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.8"
msgid "“Na kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvāma."
msgstr "“Brahmin, that’s not what we’re doing."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.9"
msgid "Kālikañca kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hitvā sandiṭṭhikaṃ anudhāvāma."
msgstr ""
"We’re giving up what takes time to chase after what we see in the present "
"life."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.10"
msgid ""
"Kālikā hi, brāhmaṇa, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo "
"ettha bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"For the Buddha says that sensual pleasures take time; they give much "
"suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks."

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.11"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo "
"viññūhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But this teaching is realizable in this very life, immediately effective, "
"inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for "
"themselves.”"

msgctxt "sn4.21:1.12"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, māro pāpimā sīsaṃ okampetvā jivhaṃ nillāletvā tivisākhaṃ nalāṭe "
"nalāṭikaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā daṇḍamolubbha pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"When they had spoken, Māra the Wicked shook his head, waggled his tongue, "
"raised his eyebrows until his brow puckered in three furrows, and departed "
"leaning on his staff."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.261"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.21:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then those senior mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said:"

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.2"
msgid ""
"“idha mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato avidūre appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharāma."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, aññataro brāhmaṇo mahantena jaṭaṇḍuvena "
"ajinakkhipanivattho jiṇṇo gopānasivaṅko ghurughurupassāsī udumbaradaṇḍaṃ "
"gahetvā yena mayaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā amhe etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.4"
msgid ""
"‘daharā bhavanto pabbajitā susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā "
"paṭhamena vayasā anikkīḷitāvino kāmesu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.5"
msgid "Bhuñjantu bhavanto mānusake kāme."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.6"
msgid "Mā sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvitthā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, mayaṃ, bhante, taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocumha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.8"
msgid "‘na kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvāma."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.9"
msgid "Kālikañca kho mayaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hitvā sandiṭṭhikaṃ anudhāvāma."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.10"
msgid ""
"Kālikā hi, brāhmaṇa, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo "
"ettha bhiyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.11"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo "
"viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.21:2.12"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, bhante, so brāhmaṇo sīsaṃ okampetvā jivhaṃ nillāletvā tivisākhaṃ "
"nalāṭe nalāṭikaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā daṇḍamolubbha pakkanto”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.21:3.1"
msgid "“Neso, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇo."
msgstr "“Mendicants, that was no brahmin."

msgctxt "sn4.21:3.2"
msgid "Māro eso pāpimā tumhākaṃ vicakkhukammāya āgato”ti."
msgstr "That was Māra the Wicked who came to pull the wool over your eyes!”"

msgctxt "sn4.21:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited this "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.262"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.1"
msgid "“Yo dukkhamaddakkhi yatonidānaṃ,"
msgstr "“When a person has seen where suffering comes from"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.2"
msgid "Kāmesu so jantu kathaṃ nameyya;"
msgstr "how could they incline towards sensual pleasures?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.3"
msgid "Upadhiṃ viditvā saṅgoti loke,"
msgstr "Realizing that attachment is a tie in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.21:4.4"
msgid "Tasseva jantu vinayāya sikkhe”ti."
msgstr "a person would train to remove it.”"
